@ijuma @granthenke 

I modified this patch
- Create de-duplicated dependant libs located at kafka/build
- Separate the dependant libs into four parts: java-dependant-libs, scala-dependant-libs, java-test-dependant-libs, scala-test-dependant-libs
- Create the symlink from de-duplicate dependant libs to project's build directory; to run script, we have to sepecify the project name in order to construct classpath only with jars needed;
- Also modified script for windows

@MayureshGharat @becketqin Okay so just to clarify:

1) Let's say the producer client is being used by multiple threads, one thread call close() which then becomes a force close, then other threads are expected to see IllegalStateException?

2) And then for MM case, when the callback gets an error and force close producer according to the config, from the logs we will see IllegalStateException following a INFO("Closing producer due to send failure.") as the producer threads may be still sending messages after processed the callback?
